The paper discusses issues related to human-computer interaction (HCI) for AI-based systems for people who are Deaf or Hard of Hearing (DHH), which falls under the category of Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC). The paper also discusses the lack of interpretability of AI systems, ethical responsibilities of access technology researchers and companies, appropriate evaluation metrics for AI-based access technologies, and the ways in which AI systems influence human behavior, which are all relevant to the sub-categories of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL), Cybersecurity (cs.CR), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Computers and Society (cs.CY).
